The paper discusses the challenges of semantics in Blockchain and Distributed Ledger Technologies, which falls under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a new approach to Blockchain/DLT, which involves the use of smart contracts that can function as legal contracts, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the potential impact of this new approach on various industries, which falls under the categories of Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Programming Languages (cs.PL).
